    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0315">
<l>akameṉ kiḷavikkuk kaimuṉ variṉē</l>
<l>mutaṉilai yoḻiya muṉṉavai keṭutalum</l>
<l>varainilai yiṉṟē yāciri yarkka</l>
<l>melleḻuttu mikuta lāvayi ṉāṉa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When <foreign xml:lang="ta">kai</foreign> ' hand ' comes after the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">akam</foreign> ' inside ',</l>
<l>leaving the first portion to remain, the disappearance</l>
<l>of those which stand before [<foreign xml:lang="ta">kai</foreign>] is not forbidden in the usage</l>
<l>of writers ;<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">Āciriyar</foreign> (cf. Skt. <foreign xml:lang="sa">ācārya,</foreign> DBIA 30) ' teacher, author, scholar '.</note> in
          that environment, the nasal is inserted.<note place="foot">Both <foreign xml:lang="ta">akaṅkai</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">
          aṅkai</foreign> ' palm ' are possible for <foreign xml:lang="ta">akam + kai</foreign> '
          inside ' + ' hand '. Iḻampūraṇar takes it rightly as <foreign xml:lang="ta">marūu</foreign> ' contraction '.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
